The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Calcutta, Dec. 24: The government will consider the merger of BSNL and MTNL based on suggestions made by a financial consultant appointed by the Centre, BSNL chairman and managing director A. K. Sinha said today. He added that the consultant had already submitted the report to the government and the issue had been under consideration. 

 New Delhi, Dec. 24: Former commerce minister Arun Jaitley today said India must not allow agriculture negotiations to move forward until rich nations agree to eliminate farm subsidies. ?Year 2013 is the last possible date under the Doha round. How can it be a big achievement,? he said at a seminar on WTO, organised by the Institute of Company Secretaries of India here.

 Mumbai, Dec. 24: Air Deccan has signed a $1.5-billion agreement with Airbus Industrie to purchase 30 more A320 planes. The deal with Airbus was signed earlier this week and the delivery would begin from 2008, Air Deccan said in a release here today.




